features: 100% Polycarbonate hard shell is engineered for impact-absorbing flexibility in a lightweight design. Stylish hard shell finish helps reduce the visibility of scratches and scuffs. Molded aluminum corner guards add impact protection to high-wear points.

Built-in TSA lock keeps contents secure and allows authorities access for inspection when needed (default code set at 0-0-0). Roomy main compartment expands 2” to maximize packing capacity when needed.
Zippered interior divider panels keep contents organized, separated and secure. Multiple accessory pockets offer built-in organization and endless packing options.

Lightweight PowerScope Lite handle locks in 2 positions (38” and 42.5”) to accommodate users of different heights. Patented Contour Grip with rubberized finish is designed for comfort when pushing spinner luggage. 8 Spinner wheels rotate 360° for superior maneuverability and a smooth glide in every direction.

Low profile top carry handle and bottom grip offer carrying convenience. Overall Dimensions: H 27.50 in x W 17.50 in x D 11.50 in, Case Dimensions: H 24.50 in x W 16.25 in x D 11.50 in, 9.9 LBS. Backed by our Travelpro Limited Lifetime Warranty.
body.description: Pack plenty without being weighed down. The Travelpro Pathways 3.0 Medium Check-in Expandable Hardside Spinner is durable but lightweight, with an ample interior, built-in organization and smooth-rolling spinner wheels. A generous interior compartment and zippered 2” expansion option offer room to pack for medium-length and long trips. Interior divider panels and multiple accessory pockets keep contents separated and organized. Designed for resilience to flex on impact, the 100% polycarbonate hard shell features an attractive finish that helps reduce the visibility of scuffs or scratches, while molded aluminum corner guards add impact protection to high-wear points. For added security, a TSA lock lets authorities securely unlock and lock the bag when needed for inspection. When it’s time to go, roll with ease on eight 360° rotating spinner wheels led by a height-adjustable Powerscope Lite handle with patented Contour Grip, rubberized for extra comfort. Backed by our Travelpro Limited Lifetime Warranty.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Travelpr49o has been an excellent brand for me
reviews.reviewText: Purchased my first Travelpro suitcase from the US Navy exchange in 1987. I have traveled to many countries and 49 states. Finally, after 36 years, one of the zippers was beginning to fail. Can't help but be loyal to the brand after that performance.This one looks great, is a bit lighter in weight, is composed of sturdier material, and the wheels rotate.If this one lasts 36 years, I'm probably no longer around so I'll put it in my will and one of my nieces/nephews is going to end up with a very good suitcase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Looked for a good hardshell since the inexpensive brand caved in after a few flights. LOVE this suitcase, it is HUGE inside and the color is fab. It has gone on 4 trips so far and still looks great!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very light, amazing maneuverability and lots of packing space.
reviews.reviewText: I travel a lot for work, have tested lots of carry-ons and this one is by far the best one.1- Yes, it is light but stable, it is easy to carrie on non flat surfaces and buts the weight down not on your arm.2- It has survived the airport handling on small planes (those which a carry-on just won't fit)3- Internal compartments avoid movement inside the luggage, bot have zippered covers so you can pack small things.So far I am very happy with it, it was a good investment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well after first replacement
reviews.reviewText: The travel case was damaged on the very first trip from NYC to SFO after receiving it. The support is very helpful, providing a replacement without any questions asked under warranty. The second one has been used for another month with a couple of international and domestic travels and is still in good shape only with normal wearing and scratches. It is very lightweight with smooth wheels on the bottom. Zippers are pretty strong when fully packed. The color is very special and can be easily identified at the airport. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This this is the best
reviews.reviewText: Best suitcase ever. Holds up to airfare and cruising. Lightweight enough to not add extra weight but sturdy as can be with 2 interior zippered halves. Going to buy the carryons next!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty well sized carry on
reviews.reviewText: The color is nice, it’s well sized carryon should fit all that is needed for short trips. Nice organizational pockets and telescoping handle is nice for different heights.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love my new suitcase and the color is awesome

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy stylish hard luggage
reviews.reviewText: Bought this smaller carry-on luggage piece for my boyfriend for Christmas to match his larger 25" travelpro luggage that was purchased several years ago. Looked for a year to find a matching piece. Very durable and the extra sturdy silver colored edges guard against damage and scratches when being handled at airports. Thank you Amazon.
